<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-01T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-01T02:00:00-05:00" n="195" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d195">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00115A P.W./2–145: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Huddle</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-01T08:00:00+01:00">February 1, 1945—8 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 2:39 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>704. American Interests—Japan. Legation’s 7433, November 9th.<note n="9" xml:id="d195fn1">Not printed; but for summary, see <ref target="frus1944v05#pg_1006">
                                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1944, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">v</hi>, p. 1006</ref>, footnote
                                    81.</note> Foreign Office note January 25th states Swiss
                                Legation, Tokyo reports it again approached Japanese Foreign Office
                                to obtain information regarding murder 17 Americans in Philippines
                                mentioned in Department’s 3532, October 16th.<note n="10" xml:id="d195fn2">
                                    <ref target="frus1944v05#pg_1006">
                                        <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 1006</ref>. In airgram
                                    A–411, March 12, 10 a.m. (740.00115A PW/3–1245), the Minister in
                                    Switzerland reported that the Swiss Legation at Tokyo had made
                                    renewed representations on March 3 to the Japanese Foreign
                                    Office with a view to obtaining the information requested in
                                    telegram 3532.</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Huddle</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>